@NODE introduction
@TITLE "ShowGirls À Introduction"


    @{b}Introduction@{ub}


    ShowGirls is yet another image viewer.

    You may ask: why?

    Well, I was using  ShowPPC  as  my image viewer, but since it
    has some problems and is not  developed anymore, I started to
    look for new  viewer. There  are  some  nice, but I wanted to
    have  some  simple image  manipulation options (don't want to
    launch  ImageFX to just resize image), and there were nothing
    as good as ShowPPC. So here it is!

    ShowGirls  combines  some  options from various image viewers
    like MiniShowPicture, ShowPPC and some others.


    @{b}Some of the key features:@{ub}

    - Easy browsing of directories (with mouse and keyboard)

    - Lots of supported file formats thanks to Datatypes system

    - Nice MagicUserInterface GUI

    - Image processing options like resizing, color balance, smoothing,
      sharpening, cropping, glowwing, noise reduction etc.

    - Saving of images in JPEG (with preview), PNG or IFF

    - Loading/displaying images with alpha channel

    - Scaling image display to fit in the window (user controlable)

    - Scrolling/zooming of big images

    - Optional bilinear filtering of the displayed image

    - Drag&drop of files/directories to be displayed

    - DOS notifications support (refreshing  of list  of files  when new
      files are copied in/ removed)

    - Thumbnailes generator (with templates)

    - Lossless JPEG transformations (for photos from digital camera
      from example)

    - Automatic rotation of images taken from digital cameras (if
      camera provides needed informations).

    - 2 directory browsing methods. Using "simple" list or list of
      thumbnails (miniature of image)

    - Thumbnails browser optimized for viewing pictures taken with digicam
	  (very fast thumbnail creation)

    - Opus Magellan-like quick search function

    - Simple file management functions like copy, move, rename, delete

    - Text inserting function (using TTengine by Grzegorz Graszewski)

    - Color picker

    - ARexx interface

    - 3D View for more eyecandy

    - Displaying of EXIF information stored in images.

@ENDNODE

@NODE requirements
@TITLE "ShowGirls À Requirements"


    @{b}Requirements@{ub}


    - MorphOS 1.x
    - hi/true color display (15/16/24/32 bits)
    - BetterBalance.mcc (can be found on Aminet)
    - LayGroup.mcc (can be found on Aminet)

    Recommend setup:

    - MorphOS 1.4+
    - 24/32 bit colour display
    - 3D drivers for perspective view

@ENDNODE

@NODE installation
@TITLE "ShowGirls À Installation"


    @{b}Installation@{ub}


    Copy ShowGirls drawer to a place you like.

@ENDNODE

@NODE startup
@TITLE "ShowGirls À Startup"


    @{b}Startup@{ub}

    
    You can start ShowGirls from Ambient or from the CLI.
 

    @{b}Ambient@{ub}

    All default MUI- and Commodity tooltypes are supported.
    
    Additionaly there are 2 tooltypes in Showgirls.icon:

      FULLSCREEN - will start a viewer in fullscreen mode:)
      
      BROWSER - will make browser panel visible at start. 

      3DVIEW - switches display mode to 3d.

    @{b}CLI@{ub}

    ShowGirls can be started  with an  image  filename as a para-
    meter. Then the image will be  displayed and the directory it
    is in will be  visible in  the  browser. If the  file part is
    ommited (only path is given) then this path will be displayed
    in the browser, but nothing will be shown.

    Additionaly  FULLSCREEN,  BROWSER and  3DVIEW params  can  be
    supplied (explained above).

@ENDNODE


@NODE usage
@TITLE "ShowGirls À General Usage"


    @{b}General usage@{ub}


    The main window of ShowGirls is divided into 2 parts. On left
    side there is the image display and  on  right  side  is  the
    hideable file and directory browser.

    By right mouse clicking on image display you can popup a menu
    to set certain options for the display.


        Auto image size

            Controls how the image is  displayed if it's  smaller
            or  bigger then  display area.  There  are  2 options
            which i don't think need additional explanation.

        Zoom

            Keep         - does not reset zoom factor when chang-
                           ing pictures.


        Filter

            None         - do not use filtering when displaying a
                           scaled image.

            Bilinear     - use bilinear filtering when displaying
                           scaled images. If will improve image.


        Contents

            Color+Alpha  - will use image's alpha channel to blend
                           with default background (default) mode

            Color        - will ignore alpha  channel information

            Alpha        - only shows  alpha channel  information

        Subtask

            When  activated  then  the  drawing will be done by a
            separate task. ShowGirls GUI is a bit more responsive
            this way.
      


    @{b}Keyboard support@{ub}

    Besides the intuitive  and self-explaining GUI ShowGirls also
    supports  a  lot  useful  keyboard  shortcuts to make picture
    browsing and showing more comfortable.

        PageUp/PageDown  - display next/previous image in current
                           directory. It will skip all non-image
                           files

        Enter/Backspace  - enter/leave a directory

        CursorDown       - displays  volumes/assigns  list,  when
                           path string is active

        -/+              - zoom  in/out image

        DEL              - deletes the selected, but not necesary
                           displayed image (it asks first).

        Shift+DEL        - deletes the selected, but not necesary
                           displayed  image  without  asking  for
                           confirmation.


    There are also some additional mouse actions:

        Mouse Rightpress on thumbnail or list entry:
                         - Displays  context  menu with  a set of
                           usefull functions.

        Mouse Rightpress on path string gadget:
                         - Displays context menu with directories
                           You were watching images from recently

        Mouse Leftpress on image display
                         - move image.

       
@ENDNODE

@NODE menuoptions
@TITLE "ShowGirls À Menuoptions"


    @{b}Menu options@{ub}


    @{b}Project@{ub}

        About...

            Opens the About window with copyright information and
            credits.

        About MUI...

            Opens MUIs About window.

        Save Image...

            Here you can export the current image to a file. This
            becomes very useful when you have done certain  mani-
            pulations to the image. In  current release ShowGirls
            supports  saving of  PNG,  JPEG and  IFF  files  with
            certain options. 

        Quit

            Quits ShowGirls immediatelly.


    @{b}Edit@{ub}

        Copy

            Copies current image  buffer into  clipboard. Unfort-
            unately  IFF/ILBM can't  store alpha channel, so it's
            not copied.

        Paste

            Inserts clipboard content into image buffer.


    @{b}View@{ub}

        Browser

            Visible

                When deactivated then the file and directory
                browser will be turned off.

            List

                Switches the directory view to use list of files.
                The list contains info about file's size, date
                and type

            Thumbnails

                Switched the directory view to use miniatures
                of images.
                

        Full screen

            When activated then ShowGirls window opens borderless
            and will use the whole screen for the display. It
            will not open custom screen. If You want to do it
            simply move the viewer to another defined MUI screen.

        EXIF Info

            If image contains  EXIF tags,  then a  window will be
            opened  to display  them. Window  hides if  displayed
            file doesn't contain tags.


    @{b}Process@{ub}

        The process menu features an extensive set of easy-to-use
        image manipulation  functions. Most  of them  have either
        a realtime preview  option  which  can  be activated or a
        "test" gadget (CPU intensive functions).

        Some notes on processing options:

        - In most cases resizing  with "Lanczos" filter will give
          the best results.

        - Median filter can be quite slow (even if it is probably
          10 times  faster then in ImageFX), so it is  not imple-
          mented as realtime


    @{b}Tools@{ub}

        Thumbnailer

            Read more in @{" Thumbnailer " link thumbnailer } section.

        JPEG Transform

            Read more in @{" JPEG Transform" link jpegtransform} section.


    @{b}Settings@{ub}

        Setup...

            Will open ShowGirls settings window. For explanation
            look in @{" Settings" link settings } section.

        MUI...

            Opens MUI Settings.



          
@ENDNODE

@NODE thumbnailer
@TITLE "ShowGirls À Thumbnailer"


    @{b}Thumbnailer@{ub}


    The Thumbnailer  is a very  useful tool which creates MorphOS
    PNG icons  with  small  previews  (so called Thumbnails)  for
    picture files  on your harddisk. You can later use Ambient to
    easily browse  your picture  collection  and show pictures in
    ShowGirls by simple double clicking on the icons of them.

    ShowGirls is  probably the first program which let you choose
    a template for  the  thumbnail  icon. You  basically  load  a
    template  (PNG  file with active alpha  channel) and then you
    define the  area  which will be used later for the downscaled
    image (thumbnail).


    Path

        The path which will be processed. ShowGirls will scan all
        files and when it detectes a picture (using  the Datatype
        system) then it will create a thumbnail icon for it.

        e.g. it finds "example.jpg" then it'll  create a PNG file
             called "example.jpg.info".

    Recursive

        When activated ShowGirls will  not only  scan "Path", but
        also all sub-directories in "Path".

    Default Tool

        The  default  tool  which will be  written  into the icon
        information. It's a good idea to select  ShowGirls itself
        here, of course :^) 

		Note: 
              Default Tool will be only inserted into a file if a 
              suffix is '.info'.

    Suffix

        Allows to specify  suffix which  will be added to created
        thumbnails.

   	Replace

	    Will first remove  old file suffix, and  then add new one
        specified in 'Suffix' field.

    Width/Height

        Defines the  size  of  the  thumbnail. Please  note  that
        ShowGirls  scales  the  images with proper aspect. Unused
        areas will stay transparent on final thumbnail.

    Preserve aspect ratio

        Enables You  to choose if  You want  to keep aspect ratio
        when resizing images. Image will be centered in specified
        area when it will be smaller after resizing.

    Template/Enable

        When  activated  ShowGirls will use a template. The temp-
        late also defines the final size of the icon. When you do
        not  use  a  template then Width/Height defines the final
        size of the icon.

    Offset X/Y

        The offset  in  the  template  where the thumbail will be
        placed on.

    Width/Height

        Allows to resize template image before composition process
        starts.



    Below the options you see 3  preview areas. In the first  you
    can see how the thumbnail will  be placed on the template. In
    the second area  you see  an example image (please select one
    first in the ShowGirls main window) and in the last  area you
    will see how the final thumbnail icon will look by using your
    current settings and  the example image. Please note that you
    can set  certain options for the preview areas by right mouse
    clicking on them.


    Finally you can initiate the creation process by pressing the
    obvious "Start" gadget.

@ENDNODE


@NODE jpegtransform
@TITLE "ShowGirls À JPEG Transform"


    @{b}JPEG Transform@{ub}

    This tool was made for all users of digital cameras who want
    to rotate or flip images without loosing their original qua-
    lity. 

    Only the basic options are available, because to allow more
    complex operations it would  be needed to decompress  image,
    process it and the compress again.  And it wouldn't be loss-
    less of course.

    The processed  image is not the one displayed in the window
    but the one selected  currently on the list. If it's  not a
    JPEG image, then tool's window will not appear.

    Some additional options are available:

        Trim non-transformable edge blocks

            Lossless operations  only work on  JPEG which dimen-
            sions are multiply of 8 or 16.  So when they are not
            some bugs in resulting image may be  visible (on the
            borders of  image).  This  option  lets You trim the
            image so this will not happen.  You will loose  some
            pixels at image edges though.

        Output file

            By default this string gadget will contain full path
            to selected  image. But if for some reason  You want
            to save it into  some different  place, here You can
            change it.

@ENDNODE


@NODE settings
@TITLE "ShowGirls À Settings"


    @{b}Settings@{ub}

    
    Because ShowGirls is getting bigger  and bigger, it was nece-
    sary to create separate window  when  all additional settings
    can be customized. In  current  version  this window contains
    two pages:

        Thumbnails

            This one is let You  customize  the thumbnails direc-
            tory list.  It  includes,  their  dimensions,  memory
            settings, cache, etc.

            Thumbnail group

                Width and height

                    Dimensions or a thumbnail.

                Border

                    Space between thumbnail image and the area it
                    resides in.

                Save memory

                    Enabled, it will reduce memory used by thumb-
                    nails images by 33%.

            Cache group

                Enable disk cache

                    Enables  disk  cache  for  thumbnails  images.
                    Next time when You will be  browsing the same
                    directory, miniatures will be loaded from the
                    cache resulting in MUCH faster scanning.

                Compression

                    Lets Yo  select  the compresion  method  that
                    will be used  when saving  thumbs in  a cache.

                    Low, Medium, High -   these  modes  use  JPEG
                           compression  with  different  quality.
                           They   produce  smallest  files   with
                           acceptable  quality  (especialy  "Low"
                           mode).

               Path

                    Is the  place on  Your HD (or in RAM: ) where
                    the cache structure will be built.

		          Disabled devices

		          On this list you can  place devices for which
                    You want to disable caching.  Good idea is to
                    put 'ram' or 'cd0' there.

               
               Maintance group


                    Calculate - will sum size of all files stored
                           in cache directory.
                    
                    Clear - remove all files from cache directory
                     
                    Remove Dead -  removes  only  thumbnails  for 
                           files  that  are  no longer  existing.

        Browser

            Lets You customize the behaviour of the file browser.
            For now there are only a few options:

                Show info files

                    Don't hide .info files

                Show non-image files

                    Don't hide  files  which  are not images.  Be
                    carefull with option, because it can greately
                    reduce directory scanning speed.

        General

            Lets You customize behaviour of various general usage
            functions.

                Change window/fullscreen on doubleclick
 
                    Function that lets you  change between window
                    and fullscreen mode on doubleclick on picture
                    display area.

                Correct image orientation

                    Some  cameras  store   orientation  of  taken
                    picture. If ShowGirls  finds this info it can
                    automaticly adjust displayed image.

                Replace file suffix

                    When saving file, ShowGirls will automaticaly
                    replace  file suffix  to the  one of selected
                    file  type: .jpg for JPEG, .png  for PNG  and
                    .iff for IFF-ILBM.
               
                Use last selected path

                    When saving a file a default path will be same
                    as the one chosen  when saving previous file,
                    instead of  the path from  where the file was
                    loaded.
                  
                Details

                    Tells  if  picture  details  group  should  be
                    visible after application is started.

                Color picker

                    Same as above, but refers to color picker.


@ENDNODE


