@NODE arexx
@TITLE "ShowGirls À Arexx interface"


    @{b}ARexx interface@{ub}


    This page contains list of currently implemented commands.
    General rule is that if command returns value, it returns
    error code, so if it returns 0 then operation succeded.

    Load FILENAME
        - loads image given as param. If directory was different
          than currentry set then it will be changed.

          Load "Media:images/image.jpg"

          Will  change  current  directory to Media:images  and
          display image.jpg from this directory.
          
    LoadNext
    LoadPrev
        - loads next/previous image in active directory.

    ChangeDirectory PATH
        - sets new active directory.

    SaveJPG FILENAME,QUALITY
        - saves loaded image as JPEG with selectable quality

          SaveJPG "ram:image.jpg" 80

          Will save currently loaded image as image.jpg in ram:


    SavePNG FILENAME,ALPHA
        - saves loaded image as PNG with optional alpha channel

    SaveIFF FILENAME
        - saves loaded image as 24bit IFF ILBM

    ImageWidth
    ImageHeight
        - returns loaded image width/height or 0 if nothing is
          loaded

    ImageDate
        - returns loaded image date or 0 if nothing is loaded.
          If image contains EXIF tags then date from the tags
          is returned.

    Scale METHOD,WIDTH,HEIGHT,RATIO,BORDER,BORDERCOLOR
        - scales loaded image. RATIO param overrides WIDTH and
          HEIGHT  params. BORDERCOLOR  param is  specified  as
          hexadecimal value like 0xAARRGGBB. METHOD is one of:
          - box
          - triangle
          - bell
          - spline
          - bilinear
          - lanczos
          - mitchell

    Crop LEFT,TOP,WIDTH,HEIGHT
        - cuts rectangle specified by params from loaded image.

    Blur METHOD,RADIUS
        - blurs  image. RADIUS  defines strength  of  blurring.
          METHOD is one of:
          - Color - blurs RGB channels only
          - Alpha - blurs Alpha channel only
          - ColorAlpha - blurs all channels (default)

    SelectiveBlur METHOD,RADIUS,THRESHOLD
        - selectively blurs  image. THRESHOLD  defines how much
          blurred  area  might  differ from  surrounding  to be
          affected. Range is 0..255. METHOD is one of:
          - Color - blurs RGB channels only
          - Alpha - blurs Alpha channel only

    Sharpen RADIUS,STRENGTH
        - sharpens image. RADIUS param  specifies size of  mask
          used for the process. STRENGTH tells how sharpened
          image is blended with original one. Range is 0...100.

    Levels METHOD,MIN,MAX
        - adjusts image histogram. METHOD is one of:
          - Color - adjusts RGB channels only
          - Alpha - adjusts Alpha channel only
          - ColorAlpha - adjusts all channels

    ClipboardCopy
        - copies loaded image into clipboard

    ClipboardPaste
        - pastes image from clipboard into buffer

    InsertText TEXT,FONT,SIZE,DIRECTION,ORIGIN,POSX,POSY,COLOR,
               SHADOW,SPOSX,SPOSY,SCOLOR,SSMOOTH,SINTENSITY
        - inserts text. FONT is filename including full path.
          DIRECTION is one of:
          - leftright
          - topbottom
          - bottomtop
          ORIGIN specifies picture corned to shich position is
          relative:
          - lefttop
          - righttop
          - leftbottom
          - rightbottom
          COLOR is hexadecimal value like 0xAARRGGB. Same for
          SCOLOR. SHADOW enables or disabled shadow effect.
          SSMOOTH is shadow smoothness and SINTENSITY it's
          intensity (0...n).       
   
@ENDNODE
